narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: MUSI 205 is a brief introduction to analysing a music text; I would recommend the course to students who have significant music theory background.
I would recommend MUSI 205 to any student who was already confident in basic music theory concepts (reading music, key signatures, etc.) and prepared to put the time/effort into applying that.
MUSI 205 is a great introduction to how a musicologist thinks. Take it with Prof. Quinn if possible, because he has a quick wit and keeps class interesting.
